Born in nc. 65, Horace was studying at Athens at the time of the death of Caesar in lae. 44 He joined Brutus, and was made military tribune, thus *occasionally at least taking the command of a legion. In ne. 43 he appears to have been with Brutus in Asia (Sat. i. 7, 18): in nc 42 be took part, , though not a very distinguished part, in me battle of Philippi. His return to Rome probably followed in the next year ; bnt some time must be supposed to have elapsed before his talents can have won for him the friendship of Vergil and Varius, and warranted them in introducing him to Maecenas.
